17/10/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The special prosecutor's office has pressed charges against five people for international trafficking of human organs and organised crime, EULEX announced on Friday (October 15th).
Among those charged are doctors and a senior official at the health ministry.
The case is related to the Medicus Clinic in Pristina, where organs were removed.
EULEX says the organ donors and recipients were different nationalities.
The investigation began in 2008.
(RTS, Tanjug, AP, AFP - 15/10/10)
